text: Àṣìṣe tí o wáyé ṣe àfikún àti ìyípadà sí ìmọ̀ orírùn, nígbàtí ìyàsọ́tọ̀ sì yọ ọ́ kúrò nínú agbami ìyípadà.

Yoruba: Orile ede Turkey je eyiti okun nla meta yi ka: okun Aegean ni apa iwo oorun, Okun Dudu ni ariwa ati Okun Medirettanean ni apa ila oorun. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Yoruba: Níbẹ̀rẹ̀ ogun wọn sábà rín àjò lọ sí òkè òkun ṣùgbọ́n bí wọn ṣe n ṣẹ̀dá rédà tí ó pé si àwọn ọkọ̀ abẹ́ omi níláti jìn sínú omí kí wọ́n ma baà rí wọn. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Yoruba: Àwọn ènìyàn tó ní irú ìrònú yìí ní ọpọlọ, wọ́n sì lè gbé ǹkan sórí, wọ́n lè yànjú ìṣòro wọ́n sì lè ṣiṣẹ́ lórí ìdánwò síẹ́nsì.

English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Yoruba: Níbẹ̀rẹ̀ ogun wọn sábà rín àjò lọ sí òkè òkun ṣùgbọ́n bí wọn ṣe n ṣẹ̀dá rédà tí ó pé si àwọn ọkọ̀ abẹ́ omi níláti jìn sínú omí kí wọ́n ma baà rí wọn. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Yoruba: Orile ede Turkey je eyiti okun nla meta yi ka: okun Aegean ni apa iwo oorun, Okun Dudu ni ariwa ati Okun Medirettanean ni apa ila oorun. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Yoruba: Níbẹ̀rẹ̀ ogun wọn sábà rín àjò lọ sí òkè òkun ṣùgbọ́n bí wọn ṣe n ṣẹ̀dá rédà tí ó pé si àwọn ọkọ̀ abẹ́ omi níláti jìn sínú omí kí wọ́n ma baà rí wọn. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Yoruba: Èyí tó gàbá lé ẹkùn àríwá ẹ̀yìn Machu Picchu ni òkè yíyọ̀, ó tún jẹ́ ìtàkùn fáwọn àwòrán. 
English: Machu Picchu is a mountain in the Andes, and is the highest peak in the world.

text: Agbègbè Turkey pẹ̀lú adágún gba bí i ààyè ọ̀rìn lé lẹ́ẹ̀dẹ́gbẹ̀rin ó lé mẹ́ta ẹgbẹ̀rún onígun mẹ́rin kìlómítà (300,948 sq mi),nínú èyí tí ọ̀tà lé lẹ́ẹ̀dẹ́gbẹ̀rin ó dín márùn ún ẹgbẹ̀rún ó lé ọ̀rìn lé lẹ́gbẹ̀ta ó lé mẹ́jọ onígun mẹ́rin kìlómítà (291,773 sq mi) ló wà ní ẹkùn ìwọ̀ oòrùn gúúsù Asia àti ẹgbẹ̀rún mẹ́tàlélógún, ọ̀tà lé lẹ́ẹ̀dẹ́gbẹ̀rin ó lé mẹ́rin onígun mẹ́rin kìlómítà (9,174 sq mi) in Europe.
